Program: Outlook
Title: 13/07/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p003kp3t
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 13 Jul 2009
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Matthew Bannister. On today's programme: Abuse in marriage; Kyrgyz migrants; and born black to white parents. Abuse in UK arranged marriages The woman from Pakistan who was treated like a slave by her mother-in-law when she came to the UK for an arranged marriage. Kyrgyz Migrants On the train with migrants from Kyrgyzstan seeking work in Russia. Sandra Laing The tragic story of the girl who looked black - but was born to white parents in apartheid South Africa. Show less